I solved by mocking the result of my `schedulerProvider.ioToMainObservableScheduler()`. 

The main problem was to work with `Schedulers.io()` and `AndroidSchedulers.mainThread()`. Then i found this amazing post on medium. [Fixing unit test issue of RxJava Chain and Kotlin][1].


So before i need to make an observable call i do this.

```
every {
    schedulerProvider.ioToMainObservableScheduler&lt;Scheduler&gt;()
} answers {
    ObservableTransformer { upstream -&gt; 
        upstream.subscribeOn(Schedulers.io()).observeOn(AndroidSchedulers.mainThread()) 
    }
}
``` 

